Police have asked anyone with information regarding the fatal shooting in Wesbank to contact Crime Stop. CAPE TOWN Police are investigating whether a shooting which claimed the life of a 13-year-old boy in Wesbank may have been gang-related.The boy was shot dead on Sunday. The Police s Frederick van Wyk says, Circumstances surrounding the shooting incident in Wesbank whereby a 13-year-old man was fatally wounded is under investigation. Anyone with information about this fatal incident is kindly requested to contact Crime Stop. (Edited by Leeto M Khoza)